This paper discusses the performance of binary classifiers in machine learning, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper specifically discusses the use of machine learning classifiers and their performance. The paper also touches on topics related to computer security, which suggests that it could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of classifiers in image recognition, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the use of logistic regression and ANNs, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence, suggesting that it could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the use of biometric data, which could place it under cs.MM (Multimedia).
